        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare primary immunodeficiency characterized by infantile onset of generalized lymphadenopathy splenomegaly and lymphocytosis with excessive polyclonal expansion of B-cells. Patients present recurrent infections and impaired T-cell and antibody responses while overt autoimmune manifestations are usually absent. Occurrence of B-cell malignancy later in life has been reported."
        },
